5–1189","about 1170":"omkring 1170","1130":"1130","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","1170":"1170","1305":"1305","1215":"1215","1259":"1259","1224":"1224","1169":"1169","1135":"1135","1189":"1189","1200":"1200","England":"England","Thurleigh, Bedfordshire, England":"Thurleigh, Bedfordshire, England"},"nl":{"about 1170–":"circa 1170–Overleden","1160–1200":"1160–1200","1170–Male":"1170–Overleden","1169–Female":"1169–Overleden","1215–1305":"1215–1305","1130–1195":"1130–1195","1135–1189":"1135–1189","about 1170":"circa 1170","1130":"1130","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","1170":"1170","1305":"1305","1215":"1215","1259":"1259","1224":"1224","1169":"1169","1135":"1135","1189":"1189","1200":"1200","England":"England","Thurleigh, Bedfordshire, England":"Thurleigh, Bedfordshire, England"},"en":{"about 1170–":"about 1170–Deceased","1160–1200":"1160–1200","1170–Male":"1170–Deceased","1169–Female":"1169–Deceased","1215–1305":"1215–1305","1130–1195":"1130–1195","1135–1189":"1135–1189","about 1170":"about 1170","1130":"1130","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","1170":"1170","1305":"1305","1215":"1215","1259":"1259","1224":"1224","1169":"1169","1135":"1135","1189":"1189","1200":"1200","England":"England","Thurleigh, Bedfordshire, England":"Thurleigh, Bedfordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hervey","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Harvey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Harvey","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): from the Old French and Middle English personal name <i>Hervei</i>, also found as <i>Herveu</i>, <i>Hervé</i>, and <i>Hervi</i>. The name <i>Herveu</i> or <i>Herv(e)i</i> was borne by a number of Bretons at the Norman Conquest and, as such, represents a French form of the Old Breton name <i>Hoiearnviu</i> or <i>Hærviu</i> (see   Herve  ). Among Normans <i>Herve(i)</i> or <i>Herv(e)i</i> was also a French form of ancient Germanic <i>Hariwic</i>, <i>Herewic</i> (from <i>hari</i> ‘army’ + <i>wīg</i> ‘war’), with intervocalic /w/ becoming /v/ in Old French. The Breton and ancient Germanic names were commonly Latinized as <i>Herve(i)us</i> and <i>Hervic(i)us</i> respectively but, since their most common vernacular forms in Old French were indistinguishable, the Latin forms were also sometimes interchangeable, especially <i>Herveus</i>.","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó hAirmheadhaigh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Airmheadhach</i>’, a personal name probably meaning ‘esteemed’. It seems to be a derivative of <i>Airmheadh</i>, the name borne by a mythological physician.","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó hEarchaidh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Earchadh</i>’, a personal name of uncertain origin."]}]},{"name":"Yuon","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Manx form of   John ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":45,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":54,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705189,"age":89,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When Yuon Hervey was born about 1170, in England, his father, Count Robert Hervey, was 41 and his mother, Matilda, was 36. He married Elizabeth Goieth. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in Thurleigh, Bedfordshire, England."},"et":{"about 1170–":"umbes 1170–Surnud","1160–1200":"1160–1200","1170–Male":"1170–Surnud","1169–Female":"1169–Surnud","1215–1305":"1215–1305","1130–1195":"1130–1195","1135–1189":"1135–1189","about 1170":"umbes 1170","1130":"1130","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","1170":"1170","1305":"1305","1215":"1215","1259":"1259","1224":"1224","1169":"1169","1135":"1135","1189":"1189","1200":"1200","England":"England","Thurleigh, Bedfordshire, England":"Thurleigh, Bedfordshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1170–":"noin 1170–Kuollut","1160–1200":"1160–1200","1170–Male":"1170–Kuollut","1169–Female":"1169–Kuollut","1215–1305":"1215–1305","1130–1195":"1130–1195","1135–1189":"1135–1189","about 1170":"noin 1170","1130":"1130","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","1170":"1170","1305":"1305","1215":"1215","1259":"1259","1224":"1224","1169":"1169","1135":"1135","1189":"1189","1200":"1200","England":"England","Thurleigh, Bedfordshire, England":"Thurleigh, Bedfordshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1170–":"environ 1170–Décédé","1160–1200":"1160–1200","1170–Male":"1170–Décédé","1169–Female":"1169–Décédée","1215–1305":"1215–1305","1130–1195":"1130–1195","1135–1189":"1135–1189","about 1170":"environ 1170","1130":"1130","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","1170":"1170","1305":"1305","1215":"1215","1259":"1259","1224":"1224","1169":"1169","1135":"1135","1189":"1189","1200":"1200","England":"Angleterre","Thurleigh, Bedfordshire, England":"Thurleigh, Bedfordshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Yuon Hervey est né environ 1170, à Angleterre, son père, Count Robert Hervey, avait 41 ans et sa mère, Matilda, avait 36 ans. Il a épousé Elizabeth Goieth. Ils ont eu a